<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  metal:use-macro="context/@@groupserver_layout/page">
  <head>
  	<title metal:fill-slot="title">
      Hidden Post (410):
      <span tal:replace="view/siteInfo/name"/>
    </title>
    <tal:block metal:fill-slot="metadata">
      <link rel="home" 
        tal:attributes="title string:${view/siteInfo/name} Homepage;
        href view/siteInfo/url" />
      <link rel="help" 
        tal:attributes="title string:${view/siteInfo/name} Help;"
        href="/help"/>
    </tal:block>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div metal:fill-slot="body" id="single-post-page"         
      tal:define="siteId view/siteInfo/id;
        gse python:modules['Products.XWFCore.XWFUtils'].get_support_email;
        supportEmail python:gse(context,siteId);">
      <h1>Hidden Post</h1>
      <!--Appologise, and state what went wrong -->
      <p>
        Sorry, but the post you want to see is hidden.
        The reason that <a href="#">an admin</a> gave for hiding
        the post is as follows.
      </p>
      <blockquote>
        <p>
          Too many turtles.
        </p>
      </blockquote>
      <!-- Give a detailed explanation about what went wrong, and -->
      <!--   what can be done.-->
      <p>
        The post can now only be seen by the administrators and the
        author of the post.
        If you think you should be able to see the post
        <a href="#"
          tal:define="m string:Hi! I wanted to see the post ${view/requested} but it is hidden. I think I should be allowed to see the post because...;
            msg python:view.quote(m)"
          tal:attributes="href string:mailto:${supportEmail}?subject=Hidden%20Post&amp;body=${msg}"
          class="email">email support</a> 
        and we will see what we can do to help.
      </p>
      <!--Lastly, give the technical details about the error. Bots may-->
      <!--find this useful.-->
      <p id="technical">Technical Description:
        <code class="error"><span class="val">410</span>
          <span class="description">Gone</span></code>;
        <span class="detail">URL: 
          <code class="val url"
            tal:content="view/requested">http://some.site</code>
      </p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>

